"""prepare.py — thin-wrapper mode for `{{ expr_slug }}`.

Generated once by `/autoresearch:setup`. READ-ONLY thereafter. The only edits
you ever make for this experiment happen in `train.py`.

Contract (see `ar` CLI §prepare.py responsibilities):
  - `build_train_loader()` / `build_val_loader()` — re-expose the host
    project's existing dataloaders (function/custom mode only).
  - `primary_spec` — {name, direction}.
  - `aux_keys`, `hard_constraints` — constants used by `ar`.
  - `extract_metrics(...)` — project-specific key extraction. Signature varies
    by metric_backend (see below).
  - `extract_metrics_from_log(log_text)` — log-scan fallback. Always present.
  - `resume_ckpt_path()` — reads program.md's `parent_ckpt` declaration.
  - 1-batch self-test at import time (function/custom mode only).

Metric backend: `{{ metric_backend }}` — see the extract_metrics body below
for the per-backend contract.
"""

